{"lemma":"ظَنُّ","slug":"ظَنُّ","root":"ظ.ن.ن","root_slug":"ظ-ن-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ن-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ظَنّ","root":"ظنن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":21},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27693","n27696"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to think, opine, suppose, conjecture","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to doubt"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to consider true, to believe (to consider likely)","examples":[{"text":"[…] قَالَ ٱلَّذِينَ يَظُنُّونَ أَنَّهُم مُّلَاقُو ٱللَّهِ كَم مِن فِئَةٍ قَلِيلَةٍ غَلَبَتْ فِئَةً كَثِيرَةً بِإِذْنِ ٱللَّهِ […]","english":"[…] But those ˹believers˺ who were certain they would meet Allah reasoned, “How many times has a small force vanquished a mighty army by the Will of Allah! […]"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deem"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ظَنَّ (ẓanna) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ðˤan.na/","/ðˤann/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27693","headword_ar":"ظَنَّ","root":"Zn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zan~N","text_ar":"ظَنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He thought, opined, supposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conjectured:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he doubted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he knew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not by ocular perception:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zan~N","text_ar":"ظَنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below:] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotu Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZun~uhu","text_ar":"اَظُنُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zan~N","text_ar":"ظَنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZ~ananotuhu","text_ar":"اِظَّنَنْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZoTananotuhu","text_ar":"اِظْطَنَنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taZan~anotuhu","text_ar":"تَظَنَّنْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taZan~ayotuhu","text_ar":"تَظَنَّيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", this last formed by changing the last"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c:] and Lh mentions, as heard from the Benoo-Suleym,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zanotu *aAka","text_ar":"ظَنْتُ ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotu *Ak","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُ ذاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought that,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalotu","text_ar":"ظَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and other instances of the dial. of Suleym. (M.) [In the first of the senses expl. above, it governs two objective complements, which are originally an inchoative and an enunciative:] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotuka zayodFA","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُكَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought thee Zeyd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought thou wast Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotu zayodFA A_iy~aAka","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُ زَيْدًا اـِيَّاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought Zeyd thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought Zeyd was thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"], denoting by a pronoun what is originally an inchoative [in the former phrase] and what is originally an enunciative [in the latter phrase]. (S, TA.) It is also used [in this sense] in the same manner as a verb signifying an oath, the Arabs giving it the same kind of complement, saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotu laEabodu","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُ لَعَبْدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi xayorN minoka","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ خَيْرٌ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought surely 'Abd-Allah was better than thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"drd","text_ar":"درد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zan~a bihi ka*aA","text_ar":"ظَنَّ بِهِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought such a thing to be in him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is used in relation to good and to evil.] It is said in the Kur [xxxiii. 10],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wataTun~uwna biA@ll~`hi A@lZ~unuwnaA","text_ar":"وَتَطُنُّونَ بِا@للّٰهِ ا@لظُّنُونَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And ye were thinking, of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"various"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thoughts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) Accord. to Sb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotu bihi","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, the place"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of my"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zan~","text_ar":"ظَنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (M.) [In all these exs. the verb denotes a state of mind between doubt and certainty, but the latter is predominant: and hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zan~a","text_ar":"ظَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He doubted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he knew, by considering with endeavour to understand, not by ocular perception;"},{"kind":"text","text":"being more frequently used in this sense than as meaning “ he doubted, ” though not so frequently as it is in the sense of “ he thought, ” whence the meaning “ he knew ” is held by some to be tropical.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aY","text_ar":"اـِنَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotu A^an~iY mulaAqK HisaAbiyaho","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُ اَنِّى مُلَاقٍ حِسَابِيَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxix. 20], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I knew"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that I should meet with my reckoning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@l~a*iyna yaZun~uwna A^an~ahumo mulaAquw","text_ar":"ا@لَّذِينَ يَظُنُّونَ اَنَّهُمْ مُلَاقُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~ihimo","text_ar":"رَبِّهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the same [ii. 43], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who know"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that they shall meet their Lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be meeters of their Lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotu maA qaAla","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُ مَا قَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I knew"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what he meant to say"},{"kind":"text","text":"by his making a sign with his hand]. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotuhu","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh, Msb,) aor. as above, (Msb,) and so the inf. n., (M,) signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I suspected him; thought evil of him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, Msb;) and (M) so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZ~ananotuhu","text_ar":"اِظَّنَنْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZoTananotuhu","text_ar":"اِظْطَنَنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiT~ananotuhu","text_ar":"اِطَّنَنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Thus, too, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZonanotuhu","text_ar":"اَظْنَنْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to several copies of the S and accord. to the CK; but this is app. a mistranscription.] In the saying of Ibn-Seereen,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo","text_ar":"لَمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY qatoli EuvomaAna","text_ar":"فِى قَتْلِ عُثْمَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuno EaliY~N yuZ~an~u","text_ar":"يَكُنْ عَلِىٌّ يُظَّنُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, K, but in the T"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kaAn","text_ar":"مَا كَان"},{"kind":"text","text":",) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Alee was not suspected"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the case of the slaying of 'Othmán"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (T,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuZ~an~u","text_ar":"يُظَّنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yufotaEalu","text_ar":"يُفْتَعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuZotan~u","text_ar":"يُظْتَنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S, K:) so says A'Obeyd: (T:) or, as some relate it, the word is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuT~an~u","text_ar":"يُطَّنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bika*aA","text_ar":"بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yuZ~an~u","text_ar":"هُوَ يُظَّنُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuT~an~u","text_ar":"يُطَّنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is suspected of such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tn","text_ar":"طن"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tananotu bizayodK","text_ar":"طَنَنْتُ بِزَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zananotu zayodFA","text_ar":"ظَنَنْتُ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I suspected Zeyd:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1925},{"kind":"text","text":"this sense the verb has a single objective complement. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","M","Mgh","S","K","TA","T"]},{"entry_id":"n27696","headword_ar":"ظَنٌّ","root":"Zn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is a simple subst. as well as an inf. n.; (TA;) and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thought, opinion, supposition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conjecture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a preponderant belief, with the admission that the contrary may be the case:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT, El-Munáwee, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a preponderating wavering between the two extremes in indecisive belief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an inference from a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"token; when strong, leading to knowledge; and when weak, not exceeding the limit of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wahom","text_ar":"وَهْم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Er-Rághib, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doubt"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uncertainty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M;) or it has this meaning also; (Er-Rághib, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqiynN","text_ar":"يَقِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and sometimes it is put in the place, (S, K,) or used in the sense, (Mgh, Msb,) of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilomN","text_ar":"عِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqiynN","text_ar":"يَقِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certainty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in which sense it is [held by some to be] tropical; (Mgh;) or it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certainty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqiynN","text_ar":"يَقِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", T, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is obtained by considering with endeavour to understand, not by ocular perception,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not such as relates to an object of sense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) and it also means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suspicion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil opinion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA: [but in this last sense,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zin~apN","text_ar":"ظِنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more common:]) as a subst., (TA,) its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZunuwnN","text_ar":"ظُنُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZaAniynu","text_ar":"اَظَانِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, TA,) the latter anomalous, or (as ISd says, TA) it may be pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uZonuwnapN","text_ar":"اُظْنُونَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this I do not know. (M, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa say~iy^u AlZ~an~i bikul~i A^aHadK","text_ar":"هُوَ سَيِّيُ الظَّنِّ بِكُلِّ اَحَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is evil in opinion of everyone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA='a Zan~uhu bifulaAnK","text_ar":"سَا=ءَ ظَنُّهُ بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His opinion of such a one was evil."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomuhu","text_ar":"عِلْمُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAl$~aYo'i ZunuwnN","text_ar":"بِالشَّىْءِ ظُنُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His knowledge is"},{"kind":"text","text":"but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinions"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning that no confidence is to be placed in him. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","S","Mgh","M","MF","TA"]}]}}